{
  "stem": "1473.1",
  "chunk_idx": 0,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.2,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "--whatever.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 0,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "You do your thing.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that was the problem with the Yale-- the Yale project, where they do tend to-- or to-- how shall I put it?-- too much of the face.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I, I think, in general.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Uh-huh.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Right, I know that.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[LAUGHS]",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Hi.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "OK, the name its Ruth, R-U-T-H, Keller, K-E double L- E-R.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 9,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Ruth Advokat.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that was spelled two, two ways.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The Polish way is A-D-W-O-K-A-T.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 10,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But we spelled it the German way, which is A-D-V-O-K-A-T.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 11,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "March 15, 1928.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 12,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In Vienna, Austria.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Well, that is the city that I lived in until we left in December, 1938.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 13,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So I was 10 years old when I left.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "[SIGHS] It tumbles.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My main memory is, of course, the apartment with my parents and the extended family-- the aunts, the uncles, the cousins.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother's family was extremely close.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "So my mother saw one of her sisters practically every single day.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "We all lived within walking distance.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It may not be walking distance in the United States.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But we walked longer distances in those days so that I was together with aunts and cousins as far back as I can remember.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] We used to go away every summer, very early in the summer, and come back in the fall-- to small, country places very often.",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "I remember some farms where my parents-- my mother would rent rooms in, in-- well, they were farms.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "But they had-- for guests, they were for city people as guests.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And I used to look forward to these summers all year long, as far as I remember.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "Because it meant freedom, animals, and beautiful countryside, really.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 14,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And I remember every fall coming back on the train and a, a feeling of grayness.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
